com.googlecode.ehcache.annotations.key
Class MessageDigestCacheKeyGenerator

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.ehcache.annotations.key.AbstractCacheKeyGenerator<String>
      com.googlecode.ehcache.annotations.key.MessageDigestCacheKeyGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
CacheKeyGenerator<String>
public class MessageDigestCacheKeyGenerator
extends AbstractCacheKeyGenerator<String>

This key generator is a good option when a secure hash of the arguments is needed or when a larger final key space is desired. As with HashCodeCacheKeyGenerator the argument hashCode is used for key generation data but instead of the simple Java hash algorithm being used any MessageDigest can be used, SHA-1 is used by default. The generated hash is base64 encoded using Base64.encodeBase64URLSafeString(byte[])

Pros Cons
Better assurance than HashCodeCacheKeyGenerator against key collisions though with the argument hashCodes being the source of the data it is still not perfect. Slower than HashCodeCacheKeyGenerator

Version:

Author:
Eric Dalquist

deepDigest

protected final void deepDigest(byte[] hashBytes,
                                MessageDigest messageDigest,
                                Object o)
Does a deep traversal, iterating over arrays, collections and maps and map entries. When a leaf in the object graph is found the appropriate digest method is called. If AbstractCacheKeyGenerator.setCheckforCycles(boolean) is true and a cycle is found nothing is appeneded to the MessageDigest the second time the object is encountered.

Parameters:
hashBytes - A byte array of length HASH_CODE_BYTE_SIZE used when converting a hash code to byte array. Passed around to avoid extra object creation.
messageDigest - The MessageDigest used to generate the file hash key
o - The object to inspect
